author: National Geographic
description:
Join D23 and go inside the magnificent Disney Wish and Disney Treasure cruise ships, and discover the pristine beauty of Disney Lookout Cay at Lighthouse Point, Disney Cruise Line's newest private island in the Bahamas.

Disney Wish
At a two-centuries-old shipyard in Germany, 144,000 tons of steel transforms into Disney’s newest cruise ship.

Lookout Cay
Take an exclusive peek at the making of Disney Cruise Line’s new Bahamian destination with the scientists and artists who made it happen.

Disney Treasure
Go behind the scenes of Disney’s new ship, from Moana’s stage debut and the familia of Plaza de Coco to the illusions of a Haunted Mansion Parlor.

author: National Geographic
description:
The Carata dos Couros waterfalls near Alto Paraíso de Goiás flow through Brazil’s Cerrado, known as the “cradle of waters.” This cascade is part of a vast network of rivers and underground aquifers that sustain South America’s largest waterways and the region’s rich biodiversity.
